"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-2024-01-01-melissa-hoskins-husband-charged-death-olympic-cyclist-hit-car\", \"text\": \"Melissa Hoskins, a two-time Olympian in track cycling, has died after being hit by a car in Adelaide, South Australia, the Australian Olympic CommitteeannouncedSunday evening. She was 32.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe AOC has expressed the utmost sadness at the loss of Olympic cyclist Melissa Hoskins after the tragic events in Adelaide,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d the committee said. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cOur condolences go to Melissa\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s family, friends and the cycling community at this extremely difficult time.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Hoskins\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s husband, Rohan Dennis, a fellow cyclist, has been charged with \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009ccausing death by dangerous driving, driving without due care and endangering life,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009daccording to ABC, Australia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s national broadcaster.  The AOC has expressed the utmost sadness at the loss of Olympic cyclist Melissa Hoskins after the tragic events in Adelaide.Our condolences go to Melissa\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s family, friends and the cycling community at this extremely difficult time.pic.twitter.com/oh8Z8w2qf8  Hoskins, 32, represented Australia in the team pursuit event in the 2012 and \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009916 Summer Olympics. She helped her country finish fourth and fifth, respectively; she also won a world championship in the event in France in 2015.  Dennis, 33, married Hoskins in 2018. The three-time Olympian, who was not named by Australian authorities, reportedly was bailed out and will appear in court on March 13.  Loading recommendations... Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Patrick Andres is a staff writer on the Breaking and Trending News team at Sports Illustrated. He joined SI in December 2022, having worked for The Blade, Athlon Sports, Fear the Sword and Diamond Digest. Andres has covered everything from zero-attendance Big Ten basketball to a seven-overtime college football game. He is a graduate of Northwestern University's Medill School of Journalism with a double major in history .  \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC. - All Rights Reserved. The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only. Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands. All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit. If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\"}"